						<summary>

						<p>In the same place as above.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Pāṇḍyadēva: Year 11 = 1276 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription records a gift of two <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamps and probably money to provide oil for them, to the god Tāntōṉṟīśvaramuḍaiyār by a certain Mukkaṇ Āṇḍāṉ, a <hi rend="italic">Veḷḷāḷa</hi> of Nambipērūr in Vaḍapariśāra-nāḍu. A <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇa</hi> named Āṇḍāṉ Śella-bhaṭṭaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tiruchchiṟṟambala-nambi of <hi rend="italic">Bhāradvajagotra</hi> and another (name lost) who had rights (of worship) in the temple seem to have accepted the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
